00:56:51,005 --> 00:56:54,565
...to descend upon the VLA facility
here in the desert of New Mexico.

768
00:56:54,928 --> 00:56:57,488
Many have come to protest,
many to pray...

769
00:56:57,765 --> 00:57:02,245
...but most have come to participate in
what's become the best show in town.

770
00:57:08,072 --> 00:57:10,512
Well, I saw the thing
coming out of the sky

771
00:57:10,909 --> 00:57:13,949
It had one long horn
and one big eye.

772
00:57:14,289 --> 00:57:16,849
I commenced to shaking
and said, "Oo-ee!"

773
00:57:17,419 --> 00:57:20,299
"Looks like
a Purple People Eater to me"

774
00:58:11,540 --> 00:58:12,980
Hail to Vega
Hail to Vega

775
00:58:19,052 --> 00:58:20,772
But they have failed!

776
00:58:21,347 --> 00:58:24,027
It's the same people who,
again and again...

777
00:58:24,351 --> 00:58:26,391
...have brought us
to the brink of destruction!

778
00:58:26,730 --> 00:58:30,250
Who've polluted our air,
who've poisoned our water!

779
00:58:31,904 --> 00:58:33,944
Now these scientists...

780
00:58:34,908 --> 00:58:36,788
...have had their chance.

781
00:58:37,078 --> 00:58:40,078
Are these the kind of people...

782
00:58:40,542 --> 00:58:44,222
...that you want
talking to your God for you?

783
00:58:48,261 --> 00:58:50,141
Efforts continue around the clock.

784
00:58:50,431 --> 00:58:53,951
But for now, almost 2 full weeks
after the message's arrival...

785
00:58:54,270 --> 00:58:57,430
...scientists here at the VLA
still have no answers...

786
00:58:57,817 --> 00:58:59,457
...only more questions.

787
00:58:59,778 --> 00:59:02,938
Jeremy Roth, CNN,
Socorro, New Mexico.

788
00:59:03,409 --> 00:59:06,649
More on the quest for the message's
meaning, after this.

789
00:59:09,584 --> 00:59:11,344
They have to line up somehow.

790
00:59:11,629 --> 00:59:13,469
This one doesn't fit, either.

791
00:59:13,799 --> 00:59:16,319
We've tried over
a million permutations.

792
00:59:16,636 --> 00:59:19,836
Always, I can only get
three corners to fit.

793
00:59:20,976 --> 00:59:23,056
I don't understand
their significance.

794
01:00:06,585 --> 01:00:07,745
Somebody broke in...

795
01:00:14,179 --> 01:00:15,179
Hello?

796
01:00:16,182 --> 01:00:19,262
Whoever you are,
you broke into the database...

797
01:00:22,400 --> 01:00:23,680
What? Now?

798
01:00:26,573 --> 01:00:27,693
Where?

799
01:00:40,760 --> 01:00:42,160
I'll be there.

800
01:01:09,803 --> 01:01:11,203
You should feel fortunate.

801
01:01:11,973 --> 01:01:13,373
He hardly lands for anyone.

802
01:01:45,147 --> 01:01:46,947
Dr. Arroway.

803
01:01:50,864 --> 01:01:52,144
I presume?

804
01:01:53,492 --> 01:01:54,612
Mr. Hadden.

805
01:01:55,996 --> 01:01:59,036
I've had my eye on you
a long time, Doctor.

806
01:02:00,044 --> 01:02:03,364
I consider you one of my
most valuable long-term investments.

807
01:02:05,343 --> 01:02:07,703
And when it comes
to my investments...

808
01:02:09,516 --> 01:02:12,076
...I always do my homework.

809
01:02:16,902 --> 01:02:18,622
Eleanor Ann Arroway...

810
01:02:18,863 --> 01:02:21,263
...born 25th August, 1964...

811
01:02:21,575 --> 01:02:23,135
...De Pere, Wisconsin.

812
01:02:23,370 --> 01:02:27,450
Mother, Joanna, died from
complications during childbirth.

813
01:02:28,335 --> 01:02:30,935
Early testing indicated
high predisposition...

814
01:02:31,215 --> 01:02:34,135
...towards science and mathematics.

815
01:02:34,928 --> 01:02:36,088
Father, Theodore...

816
01:02:36,305 --> 01:02:39,705
...advised to provide enrichment
activities in these areas...

817
01:02:40,103 --> 01:02:42,623
...did so conscientiously
until his death...

818
01:02:42,899 --> 01:02:46,699
...from myocardial infarction,
November 10, 1974.

819
01:02:48,240 --> 01:02:51,440
You graduated from high school
in 1979...

820
01:02:51,828 --> 01:02:53,708
...almost two full years early.

821
01:02:55,250 --> 01:02:57,130
Awarded full scholarship, M.I.T...

822
01:02:57,378 --> 01:02:59,498
...graduated magna cum laude.

823
01:03:00,550 --> 01:03:02,190
Doctoral work, Cal Tech...

824
01:03:02,427 --> 01:03:05,427
...where you worked
on the lanthanide-doped ruby maser...

825
01:03:05,766 --> 01:03:09,966
...dramatically increasing
the sensitivity of radio telescopes.

826
01:03:10,564 --> 01:03:14,004
Subsequently offered a teaching
position at Harvard University...

827
01:03:14,320 --> 01:03:17,320
...which you turned down
to pursue SETI work...

828
01:03:17,616 --> 01:03:20,976
...at the Arecibo Observatory
in Puerto Rico.

829
01:03:23,458 --> 01:03:25,858
Changes in N.S.F. policy...

830
01:03:26,421 --> 01:03:29,621
...gave rise to certain
funding problems...

831
01:03:30,802 --> 01:03:32,242
...at which point...

832
01:03:32,805 --> 01:03:34,725
...you came to my attention.

833
01:03:36,185 --> 01:03:38,385
You compromised our security codes.

834
01:03:40,817 --> 01:03:42,577
Once upon a time...

835
01:03:44,656 --> 01:03:46,696
...I was a hell of an engineer.

836
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:49,080
Please, sit, Doctor.

837
01:03:49,789 --> 01:03:50,829
I have guests so rarely...

838
01:03:51,041 --> 01:03:54,201
...it's important
they feel welcome in my home.

839
01:03:55,380 --> 01:03:56,660
You live here?

840
01:03:58,343 --> 01:04:01,543
I find it convenient
to keep my interests...

841
01:04:03,017 --> 01:04:03,977
...mobile.

842
01:04:06,689 --> 01:04:10,689
Anyway, I've had my fill
of life on the ground.

843
01:04:12,656 --> 01:04:14,136
I guess I should...

844
01:04:14,826 --> 01:04:18,226
I guess I should thank you for
having bailed me out all that time.

845
01:04:23,714 --> 01:04:25,794
I know a good bet when I see one.

846
01:04:28,262 --> 01:04:30,942
Earl Grey.
No sugar, no milk, I believe.

847
01:04:34,396 --> 01:04:36,196
What am I doing here?

848
01:04:46,581 --> 01:04:49,621
The powers that be
have been very busy lately...

849
01:04:50,587 --> 01:04:52,347
...positioning themselves...

850
01:04:52,631 --> 01:04:55,311
...for the game of the millennium.

851
01:05:02,270 --> 01:05:04,790
Maybe I can help deal you back in.

852
01:05:06,276 --> 01:05:08,476
I didn't realize that I was out.

853
01:05:09,114 --> 01:05:10,874
No. Maybe not out...

854
01:05:12,118 --> 01:05:14,358
...but certainly
being handed your hat.

855
01:05:19,838 --> 01:05:23,438
I've had a long time
to make enemies, Doctor.

856
01:05:27,140 --> 01:05:28,700
There are many governments...

857
01:05:28,976 --> 01:05:30,456
...business interests...

858
01:05:31,146 --> 01:05:34,986
...even religious leaders that would
like to see me depart this earth.

859
01:05:36,654 --> 01:05:39,054
And I'll grant them their wish
soon enough.

860
01:05:39,659 --> 01:05:43,179
But before I do,
I wish to make a small contribution.

861
01:05:44,166 --> 01:05:48,486
A final gesture of goodwill to the
people of this planet who have given...

862
01:05:51,510 --> 01:05:54,070
...from whom I have taken so much.

863
01:05:57,644 --> 01:05:59,084
You found the primer.

864
01:06:01,524 --> 01:06:02,644
Clever girl!

865
01:06:03,819 --> 01:06:04,579
Lights.

866
01:06:13,208 --> 01:06:15,808
Pages and pages of data.

867
01:06:16,547 --> 01:06:19,427
Over 63,000 in all.

868
01:06:19,843 --> 01:06:21,923
And on the perimeter of each...

869
01:06:22,222 --> 01:06:25,622
Alignment symbols, registration
marks, but they don't line up.

870
01:06:26,269 --> 01:06:27,429
They do...

871
01:06:27,771 --> 01:06:29,451
...if you think like a Vegan.

872
01:06:30,442 --> 01:06:33,282
An alien intelligence
has got be more advanced...

873
01:06:33,572 --> 01:06:37,412
...and that means efficiency
functioning on multiple levels...

874
01:06:37,786 --> 01:06:39,546
...and in multiple...

875
01:06:39,831 --> 01:06:41,591
...dimensions.

876
01:06:45,589 --> 01:06:47,509
Yes, of course!

877
01:06:48,218 --> 01:06:49,218
Where's the primer?

878
01:06:49,762 --> 01:06:51,042
You'll see.

879
01:06:51,598 --> 01:06:55,918
Every three-dimensional page
contains a piece of the primer.

880
01:06:58,275 --> 01:07:01,635
There it was all the time,
staring you in the face.

881
01:07:02,907 --> 01:07:06,787
Buried within the message itself
is the key to decoding it.

882
01:07:07,246 --> 01:07:10,486
Within the layering of the matrix,
we have these basic equations:

883
01:07:12,337 --> 01:07:16,177
So with this very elementary foundation,
they have given us a kind of...

884
01:07:16,635 --> 01:07:18,875
...general scientific vocabulary.

885
01:07:19,180 --> 01:07:21,420
We now have the symbols
for true and false...

886
01:07:21,684 --> 01:07:22,924
This was the key...

887
01:07:23,186 --> 01:07:25,546
...that allowed us to decipher
their language...

888
01:07:25,857 --> 01:07:29,457
...for physics, geometry, chemistry.
Next frame, Ellie.

889
01:07:30,948 --> 01:07:34,588
Yes, and when we apply this
to the rest of the message...

890
01:07:35,663 --> 01:07:36,623
...we find this.

891
01:07:41,171 --> 01:07:44,491
Those look like engineering
schematics, almost like blueprints.

892
01:07:46,012 --> 01:07:46,972
Yes.

893
01:07:47,305 --> 01:07:50,465
It is our belief that
the message contains instructions...

894
01:07:50,810 --> 01:07:54,130
...for building something,
some kind of machine.

895
01:07:54,691 --> 01:07:57,251
A machine?
That does what, Doctor?

896
01:07:57,696 --> 01:07:59,856
We don't know.
It might be some type...

897
01:08:00,867 --> 01:08:05,347
...of advanced communication device,
or a teaching machine of some kind.

898
01:08:06,917 --> 01:08:08,197
Or it might be...

899
01:08:08,587 --> 01:08:10,187
...some kind of a transport.

900
01:08:10,715 --> 01:08:13,115
-Transport?
-There's no proof of that.

901
01:08:13,427 --> 01:08:16,867
The fact is you don't know
what it does. It could be anything.

902
01:08:17,350 --> 01:08:20,590
A Trojan Horse. We build it
and out pours the entire Vegan army.

903
01:08:21,022 --> 01:08:23,422
Why risk the personnel?
It could be a weapon.

904
01:08:23,734 --> 01:08:25,974
Right.
Some kind of a Doomsday Machine.

905
01:08:26,238 --> 01:08:28,558
Every time they detect
a new civilization...

906
01:08:28,825 --> 01:08:31,105
...they fax
construction plans from space.

907
01:08:31,412 --> 01:08:34,892
We poor saps build this thing
and blow ourselves to kingdom come.

908
01:08:35,251 --> 01:08:38,731
There's no reason to believe
their intentions are hostile.

909
01:08:39,257 --> 01:08:42,617
Why is it the egghead position
that aliens are always benign?

910
01:08:43,680 --> 01:08:45,160
We pose no threat to them.

911
01:08:45,433 --> 01:08:47,873
It'd be like us
going out of our way...

912
01:08:48,270 --> 01:08:49,870
...to destroy microbes
on an anthill.

913
01:08:50,148 --> 01:08:51,588
Interesting analogy.

914
01:08:52,193 --> 01:08:53,153
How guilty would we feel...

915
01:08:53,403 --> 01:08:56,043
...if we destroyed a few microbes
on an anthill?

916
01:08:56,407 --> 01:08:57,527
I hope you're right.

917
01:08:57,868 --> 01:08:58,868
I really do.

918
01:08:59,119 --> 01:09:02,479
But my job is to protect American
lives from any threat...

919
01:09:02,791 --> 01:09:04,831
...so I am obligated
to assume the worst.

920
01:09:05,128 --> 01:09:07,048
Yes, and I am forced
to agree with you.

921
01:09:07,340 --> 01:09:08,740
My problem is this:

922
01:09:09,468 --> 01:09:12,548
The content of that message
is morally ambiguous at best.

923
01:09:13,307 --> 01:09:16,667
Our internal numbers show
support for this is incredibly soft.

924
01:09:17,021 --> 01:09:19,581
If the President
stays this course...

925
01:09:19,858 --> 01:09:22,538
...his numbers will be going
south like ducks in winter.

926
01:09:22,946 --> 01:09:23,946
This is nuts!

927
01:09:24,156 --> 01:09:25,116
Excuse me...

928
01:09:25,366 --> 01:09:26,326
...Miss.

929
01:09:26,869 --> 01:09:29,269
We know nothing
of these creatures' values.

930
01:09:29,706 --> 01:09:32,026
We don't even know
whether they believe in God.

931
01:09:32,335 --> 01:09:34,095
This doesn't make any sense. If...

932
01:09:34,338 --> 01:09:36,098
Excuse me, Dr. Arroway.

933
01:09:36,341 --> 01:09:38,741
We won't be suppressing
any opinions here today.

934
01:09:39,721 --> 01:09:41,761
No, of course not.
I understand.

935
01:09:42,850 --> 01:09:44,250
What I meant to say...

936
01:09:44,895 --> 01:09:47,935
...is the message was written
in the language of science.

937
01:09:48,525 --> 01:09:51,725
If it was religious in nature,
it should have taken the form...

938
01:09:52,031 --> 01:09:54,631
...of a burning bush
or a voice from the sky.

939
01:09:54,910 --> 01:09:56,950
But a voice from the sky...

940
01:09:58,123 --> 01:10:00,603
...is exactly what you found,
Doctor Arroway.

941
01:10:04,382 --> 01:10:06,022
I'm sorry I'm late, ma'am.

942
01:10:07,887 --> 01:10:11,567
I agree with Mr. Rank
that there are unavoidable...

943
01:10:11,893 --> 01:10:13,973
...religious implications at stake.

944
01:10:14,230 --> 01:10:16,550
But that doesn't justify
being an alarmist.

945
01:10:18,611 --> 01:10:20,851
I hope that we can find
a common ground...

946
01:10:21,407 --> 01:10:24,327
...break through obstacles
that may have kept us apart.

947
01:10:25,413 --> 01:10:27,693
Listen, I need to make
one thing very clear.

948
01:10:28,042 --> 01:10:32,562
Our organization will not be placated
with flowery New Age rhetoric...

949
01:10:33,467 --> 01:10:34,267
Mr. President!

950
01:10:36,888 --> 01:10:38,888
The President
met with top advisors...

951
01:10:39,183 --> 01:10:42,343
...regarding the latest efforts
to decode the message.

952
01:10:42,730 --> 01:10:47,130
While there has been some progress,
the official line remains cautious.

953
01:10:47,529 --> 01:10:49,529
If you're asking
when we'll find out...

954
01:10:49,866 --> 01:10:52,106
... what the purpose
of that Machine is...

955
01:10:53,204 --> 01:10:55,804
...maybe tomorrow,
maybe next year, maybe never.

956
01:11:00,340 --> 01:11:04,740
There he is. The man with his finger
on the nation's spiritual pulse.

957
01:11:06,265 --> 01:11:07,865
It's so good to see you.

958
01:11:08,184 --> 01:11:09,224
You too.

959
01:11:10,939 --> 01:11:14,779
Your discovery, all of this.
It must be a real vindication.

960
01:11:15,612 --> 01:11:17,212
I'm really happy for you.

961
01:11:17,949 --> 01:11:18,909
Are you?

962
01:11:19,117 --> 01:11:21,437
Mr. Joss, the President's waiting.

963
01:11:24,417 --> 01:11:25,897
The President's waiting.

964
01:11:30,300 --> 01:11:31,780
See you at the reception?

965
01:11:32,470 --> 01:11:34,070
Yeah, I wouldn't miss it.

966
01:11:46,241 --> 01:11:48,441
Miss Constantine,
may I speak to you?

967
01:11:48,786 --> 01:11:50,106
Certainly.

968
01:11:51,957 --> 01:11:53,517
I have a big problem.

969
01:11:56,005 --> 01:11:58,445
Do you know where I can find
a really great dress?

970
01:12:18,246 --> 01:12:22,086
God created man in the form of
Himself, not in the form of monkeys!

971
01:12:30,973 --> 01:12:33,293
Get a job!
Don't waste my tax dollars!

972
01:12:59,891 --> 01:13:01,451
You look beautiful, Ellie.

973
01:13:03,187 --> 01:13:05,387
-So do you.
-You really do.

974
01:13:09,196 --> 01:13:10,556
I read your book.

975
01:13:11,616 --> 01:13:12,776
Here we go.

976
01:13:13,285 --> 01:13:14,765
You want me to quote you?

977
01:13:15,539 --> 01:13:16,859
"Ironically...

978
01:13:17,166 --> 01:13:19,086
...the thing people are
most hungry for...

979
01:13:19,378 --> 01:13:20,578
...meaning...

980
01:13:20,838 --> 01:13:23,998
...is the one thing science
hasn't been able to give them."

981
01:13:24,343 --> 01:13:25,303
Yeah.

982
01:13:27,682 --> 01:13:29,602
It's like you're saying that...

983
01:13:30,018 --> 01:13:32,218
...science killed God.

984
01:13:32,689 --> 01:13:35,409
What if science simply revealed...

985
01:13:36,111 --> 01:13:38,471
...that He never existed
in the first place?

986
01:13:42,036 --> 01:13:44,116
I think we need to get some air.

987
01:13:45,207 --> 01:13:46,967
And a few more of these.

988
01:13:48,587 --> 01:13:49,707
Thank you.

989
01:13:51,717 --> 01:13:53,197
A little chilly out here.

990
01:13:53,511 --> 01:13:54,911
Yeah, this is nice.

991
01:13:55,264 --> 01:13:56,424
I got one for you.

992
01:13:56,683 --> 01:13:58,283
Occam's Razor. Ever heard of it?

993
01:13:58,560 --> 01:14:01,120
Hoccam's Razor.
Sounds like some slasher movie.

994
01:14:01,440 --> 01:14:05,000
No, Occam's Razor is a basic
scientific principle which says:

995
01:14:05,404 --> 01:14:08,604
Things being equal, the simplest
explanation tends to be right.

996
01:14:09,076 --> 01:14:10,196
Makes sense to me.

997
01:14:10,745 --> 01:14:11,825
So what's more likely?

998
01:14:12,122 --> 01:14:13,082
Thank you.

999
01:14:13,708 --> 01:14:16,228
An all-powerful God
created the universe...

1000
01:14:16,545 --> 01:14:19,385
...then decided not to give
any proof of His existence?

1001
01:14:19,717 --> 01:14:20,757
Or...

1002
01:14:21,094 --> 01:14:24,174
...that He doesn't exist at all
and that we created Him...

1003
01:14:24,557 --> 01:14:26,997
...so we wouldn't feel
so small and alone.

1004
01:14:28,021 --> 01:14:29,141
I don't know.

1005
01:14:29,398 --> 01:14:33,238
I couldn't imagine living in a world
where God didn't exist.

1006
01:14:34,238 --> 01:14:35,678
I wouldn't want to.

1007
01:14:36,408 --> 01:14:38,648
How do you know
you're not deluding yourself?

1008
01:14:39,579 --> 01:14:40,699
I mean, for me...

1009
01:14:40,915 --> 01:14:42,675
...l'd need proof.

1010
01:14:43,752 --> 01:14:44,712
Proof?

1011
01:14:47,967 --> 01:14:49,567
Did you love your father?

1012
01:14:50,762 --> 01:14:52,362
Your dad, did you love him?

1013
01:14:53,600 --> 01:14:55,680
Yes. Very much.

1014
01:14:59,275 --> 01:15:00,395
Prove it.

1015
01:15:07,537 --> 01:15:08,577
Kent.

1016
01:15:09,331 --> 01:15:10,731
The White House.

1017
01:15:13,796 --> 01:15:17,636
No excuses. Whoever's responsible,
I want their head on a platter.

1018
01:15:18,178 --> 01:15:19,338
What happened?

1019
01:15:19,972 --> 01:15:21,412
You were right all along.

1020
01:15:21,808 --> 01:15:24,488
The team at the VLA
has worked around the clock...

1021
01:15:24,813 --> 01:15:27,213
...and the hard work
has finally paid off.

1022
01:15:27,859 --> 01:15:31,499
This key section uncovered tonight,
and obtained exclusively by CNN...

1023
01:15:31,823 --> 01:15:34,303
...shows an illustration
of a human figure...

1024
01:15:34,660 --> 01:15:37,380
...inside a geometric structure
of some kind.

1025
01:15:37,665 --> 01:15:39,425
This and other contextual clues...

1026
01:15:39,835 --> 01:15:42,635
...now lead scientists to believe
the message is, in fact...

1027
01:15:43,006 --> 01:15:44,726
President called
an emergency meeting.

1028
01:15:44,967 --> 01:15:46,487
I imagined he would.

1029
01:15:46,720 --> 01:15:49,720
...designed to take a single human
occupant into space...

1030
01:15:50,267 --> 01:15:52,467
...presumably to the star Vega.

1031
01:16:16,263 --> 01:16:17,343
Tell me.

1032
01:16:17,974 --> 01:16:19,014
They will build it.

1033
01:16:19,268 --> 01:16:20,028
Who goes?

1034
01:16:20,311 --> 01:16:23,631
The President's gone international
to spread the risk and cost...

1035
01:16:23,983 --> 01:16:24,863
Who goes?

1036
01:16:25,694 --> 01:16:27,294
Well, it's complicated.

1037
01:16:28,740 --> 01:16:32,100
They have formed
a group of international candidates.

1038
01:16:32,412 --> 01:16:34,332
Now, it's your discovery.

1039
01:16:34,916 --> 01:16:38,436
They understand that. You're
at the top of a very short list.

1040
01:16:38,922 --> 01:16:41,402
But they're also forming
a selection committee.

1041
01:16:41,717 --> 01:16:45,717
It's made of scholars, theologians,
scientists, philosophers...

1042
01:16:46,099 --> 01:16:47,059
You're on it.

1043
01:16:48,311 --> 01:16:49,471
I've been asked, yes.

1044
01:16:52,442 --> 01:16:54,042
I guess that means...

1045
01:16:54,737 --> 01:16:57,457
...that you're a selector,
I'm a selectee and we can't...

1046
01:16:57,783 --> 01:16:58,863
Yeah.

1047
01:16:59,118 --> 01:17:01,358
What you don't understand,
Ellie, is...

1048
01:17:01,747 --> 01:17:02,907
I understand.

1049
01:17:04,459 --> 01:17:08,299
I want you to know, whatever
happens, as far as I'm concerned...

1050
01:17:12,096 --> 01:17:13,296
Good luck.

1051
01:17:17,645 --> 01:17:21,005
Whatever you do, make sure
he doesn't monopolize the committee.

1052
01:17:21,484 --> 01:17:23,404
He is not on the committee, Ellie.

1053
01:17:27,493 --> 01:17:30,373
He just resigned.
He wants to be the one to go.

1054
01:17:32,626 --> 01:17:35,786
The President is already feeling
the financial pinch.

1055
01:17:36,214 --> 01:17:39,214
Sources say the cost of the project
is spiraling...

1056
01:17:39,511 --> 01:17:42,191
...to more than a third
of a trillion dollars...

1057
01:17:42,515 --> 01:17:45,715
...making this perhaps
the most expensive single project...

1058
01:17:46,021 --> 01:17:47,861
...in all of human history.

1059
01:17:48,149 --> 01:17:50,029
Months of debate finally reached...

1060
01:17:50,360 --> 01:17:54,640
...a conclusion last week as 10
candidates were selected by the I.M.C...

1061
01:17:55,201 --> 01:17:58,721
...representing a cross section
of political and religious views.

1062
01:17:59,081 --> 01:18:01,601
Many are the same experts
who have consulted...

1063
01:18:01,919 --> 01:18:04,119
...on the Machine's design
and function.

1064
01:18:04,423 --> 01:18:08,463
They will actively participate on-site,
during the construction process.

1065
01:18:09,096 --> 01:18:12,096
The choice of these 10 candidates
has been controversial.

1066
01:18:12,476 --> 01:18:15,116
One-third of the candidates
are American.

1067
01:18:15,481 --> 01:18:18,121
And many
international observers ask why.

1068
01:18:18,735 --> 01:18:21,295
The U.S. is shouldering
a large part of the cost...

1069
01:18:21,573 --> 01:18:24,453
Isn't it true that contractors,
like Hadden Industries...

1070
01:18:24,744 --> 01:18:27,944
...are making contributions
in exchange for technology rights?

1071
01:18:28,249 --> 01:18:31,649
Different nations are being
compensated in different ways.

1072
01:18:32,047 --> 01:18:36,407
Japan made headlines by opting
to forego candidate representation...

1073
01:18:36,887 --> 01:18:39,807
...in exchange for the
systems integration subcontract.

1074
01:18:40,225 --> 01:18:41,865
On what basis do you choose...

1075
01:18:42,103 --> 01:18:44,903
...a human being
to represent humanity?

1076
01:18:45,233 --> 01:18:46,353
Good question, Larry.

1077
01:18:46,610 --> 01:18:48,210
If nothing else...

1078
01:18:48,738 --> 01:18:52,578
...it should be somebody fluent in the
language the message was given in.

1079
01:18:52,911 --> 01:18:54,071
Science, in this case.

1080
01:18:54,747 --> 01:18:57,027
Despite your obvious enthusiasm...

1081
01:18:57,334 --> 01:18:59,534
...there's been
a lot of criticism...

1082
01:18:59,796 --> 01:19:02,356
...that this endeavor
is simply too dangerous.

1083
01:19:02,633 --> 01:19:04,993
Some of that criticism
from scientists.

1084
01:19:05,304 --> 01:19:07,984
One Nobel Prize winner noted,
his words:

1085
01:19:08,851 --> 01:19:10,571
"There is every indication...

1086
01:19:10,812 --> 01:19:14,492
...that this is beyond our capabilities,
that this endeavor will fail...

1087
01:19:14,818 --> 01:19:18,178
...and that the Machine's occupant
will pay for it with his life. "

1088
01:19:18,532 --> 01:19:20,212
How do you respond?

1089
01:19:20,535 --> 01:19:23,695
This message is from a civilization
that may be anywhere...

1090
01:19:24,040 --> 01:19:27,640
...from hundreds to millions
and millions of years ahead of us.

1091
01:19:28,004 --> 01:19:31,044
I have to believe that
an intelligence that advanced...

1092
01:19:31,843 --> 01:19:33,483
...knows what they're doing.

1093
01:19:34,973 --> 01:19:38,173
Now all it requires
on our part is...

1094
01:19:38,937 --> 01:19:39,897
Faith?

1095
01:19:43,026 --> 01:19:45,026
I was going to say,
a sense of adventure.

1096
01:19:45,321 --> 01:19:46,681
And in breaking news...

1097
01:19:47,074 --> 01:19:48,314
...astronaut John Russell...

1098
01:19:48,618 --> 01:19:52,338
...considered to be the leading American
candidate for the Machine seat...

1099
01:19:52,707 --> 01:19:54,867
...has dropped out of the running.

1100
01:19:55,378 --> 01:19:58,298
Russell met with reporters today
at his Houston home.

1101
01:19:58,841 --> 01:20:00,801
I told my dad I didn't want him...

1102
01:20:01,720 --> 01:20:02,680
...to go.

1103
01:20:02,931 --> 01:20:04,371
Daddy, don't go.

1104
01:20:07,354 --> 01:20:08,994
Nothing would give me more pride...

1105
01:20:09,273 --> 01:20:10,353
...than to...

1106
01:20:11,068 --> 01:20:12,988
...represent my country.

1107
01:20:13,404 --> 01:20:15,044
But what can I say to this?

1108
01:20:16,075 --> 01:20:19,675
Consortium officials had no comment,
but inside sources...

1109
01:20:20,039 --> 01:20:21,919
...have disclosed
that Dr. Arroway...

1110
01:20:22,209 --> 01:20:26,049
...appears to now be the
front-runner for the Machine seat.

1111
01:20:27,300 --> 01:20:29,660
"Meet me at noon.
Must talk."

1112
01:20:30,054 --> 01:20:32,174
I didn't expect a message
like this from you.

1113
01:20:32,474 --> 01:20:33,754
Thanks for coming.

1114
01:20:34,060 --> 01:20:36,860
Is this kosher?
Fraternizing with the enemy?

1115
01:20:37,189 --> 01:20:40,229
Selectors and selectees
mingling around?

1116
01:20:40,903 --> 01:20:42,623
Can we talk about Einstein?

1117
01:20:43,240 --> 01:20:44,760
Yeah, sure.

1118
01:20:45,493 --> 01:20:48,653
Special relativity.
This Machine...

1119
01:20:50,292 --> 01:20:54,212
...if it works, and you travel
to Vega at the speed of light...

1120
01:20:54,632 --> 01:20:56,672
-...when you come back...
-lf you come back.

1121
01:20:59,097 --> 01:21:00,737
If you come back...

1122
01:21:01,266 --> 01:21:05,386
...you'll be 4 years older, but over 50
years will have passed here on Earth.

1123
01:21:05,731 --> 01:21:07,051
Basically.

1124
01:21:07,943 --> 01:21:10,303
And everybody that you care about...

1125
01:21:11,365 --> 01:21:13,685
...will be gone, dead and buried.

1126
01:21:14,619 --> 01:21:18,059
If you came back,
if you survived at all...

1127
01:21:19,877 --> 01:21:23,557
Look, Palmer, nobody's saying
this isn't dangerous.

1128
01:21:23,883 --> 01:21:27,843
The rest of the candidates and myself
understand the risks we're taking.

1129
01:21:28,223 --> 01:21:29,183
Why?

1130
01:21:29,516 --> 01:21:32,076
It's a historic opportunity.
The world needs...

1131
01:21:32,396 --> 01:21:34,956
You, Ellie. You!
You personally.

1132
01:21:36,068 --> 01:21:38,748
By doing this,
you're willing to give your life.

1133
01:21:39,072 --> 01:21:41,152
You're willing to die for it.

1134
01:21:43,078 --> 01:21:44,278
Why?

1135
01:21:48,085 --> 01:21:51,725
From as long as I can remember,
I've been searching for...

1136
01:21:52,425 --> 01:21:54,065
...something...

1137
01:21:54,345 --> 01:21:57,945
...some reason why we're here.
What are we doing here? Who are we?

1138
01:21:59,102 --> 01:22:02,862
If this is a chance to find out
even a part of that answer...

1139
01:22:04,526 --> 01:22:07,406
I don't know,
I think it's worth a human life.

1140
01:22:08,198 --> 01:22:09,318
Don't you?

1141
01:22:16,252 --> 01:22:18,812
You're an incredibly brave woman,
Ellie.

1142
01:22:21,635 --> 01:22:23,475
Or incredibly nuts.

1143
01:22:53,265 --> 01:22:55,025
I'm really confused.

1144
01:22:56,478 --> 01:22:57,718
So am I.

1145
01:22:58,940 --> 01:23:02,420
I think I speak for us all
when I thank you for your patience.

1146
01:23:02,821 --> 01:23:06,061
Myself, I have one
final question, Dr. Arroway.

1147
01:23:07,786 --> 01:23:09,986
If you should meet these Vegans...

1148
01:23:10,290 --> 01:23:14,370
...and were permitted only
one question to ask of them...

1149
01:23:14,713 --> 01:23:16,313
...what would it be?

1150
01:23:18,010 --> 01:23:19,810
I suppose it would be:

1151
01:23:20,054 --> 01:23:21,654
"How did you do it?

1152
01:23:22,308 --> 01:23:26,548
How did you evolve? How did you
survive technological adolescence...

1153
01:23:26,939 --> 01:23:28,859
...without destroying yourself?"

1154
01:23:29,568 --> 01:23:34,288
That more than any other question is
one I personally would like answered.

1155
01:23:34,868 --> 01:23:36,588
Not too bad, Mike.

1156
01:23:37,330 --> 01:23:38,570
I join Dr. Bergeron...

1157
01:23:38,874 --> 01:23:42,074
...in expressing thanks for
your patience, Dr. Arroway.

1158
01:23:42,421 --> 01:23:44,901
We're all impressed
with your candor...

1159
01:23:45,341 --> 01:23:46,821
...and your stamina.

1160
01:23:47,344 --> 01:23:50,544
I think we're ready to move on
to your final statement.

1161
01:23:50,891 --> 01:23:52,651
I have one more question.

1162
01:23:52,978 --> 01:23:54,458
Yes, Mr. Joss.

1163
01:23:58,528 --> 01:24:00,808
Would you consider yourself...

1164
01:24:01,365 --> 01:24:03,605
...a spiritual person?

1165
01:24:09,127 --> 01:24:11,287
I don't understand
the point of the question.

1166
01:24:12,715 --> 01:24:15,355
I consider myself a moral person.

1167
01:24:15,720 --> 01:24:20,120
We're sure that's the case, but what
Mr. Joss is in fact asking...

1168
01:24:20,477 --> 01:24:22,237
Do you believe in God?

1169
01:24:30,825 --> 01:24:32,945
As a scientist...

1170
01:24:33,412 --> 01:24:36,692
...I rely on empirical evidence,
and in this matter...

1171
01:24:37,168 --> 01:24:40,368
...I don't believe
that there's data either way.

1172
01:24:41,341 --> 01:24:45,181
So your answer would in fact be
that you don't believe in God.

1173
01:24:49,186 --> 01:24:52,146
I don't understand the relevance
of the question.

1174
01:24:55,194 --> 01:24:58,114
95%%% of the world's population...

1175
01:24:58,449 --> 01:25:02,049
...believes in a Supreme Being
in one form or another.

1176
01:25:03,373 --> 01:25:06,493
I believe that makes the question
more than relevant.

1177
01:25:21,024 --> 01:25:22,504
I believe...

1178
01:25:26,908 --> 01:25:29,388
I believe I've already
answered that question.

1179
01:25:33,501 --> 01:25:36,781
I'm proud of what
we've achieved as a species...

1180
01:25:37,215 --> 01:25:39,135
...and as a civilization.

1181
01:25:40,845 --> 01:25:43,365
I would hate to see
everything we stand for...

1182
01:25:43,682 --> 01:25:47,242
...all that we have fought for
for a thousand generations...

1183
01:25:47,605 --> 01:25:49,925
...all that God
has blessed us with...

1184
01:25:51,360 --> 01:25:52,800
...betrayed...

1185
01:25:53,781 --> 01:25:58,261
...in the final hour because we sent a
representative who did not put our...

1186
01:25:58,955 --> 01:26:01,595
...most cherished beliefs first.

1187
01:26:04,964 --> 01:26:06,124
Thank you.

1188
01:26:39,431 --> 01:26:40,711
Why'd you do it?

1189
01:26:45,357 --> 01:26:49,317
Our job was to select someone
to speak for everybody.

1190
01:26:52,868 --> 01:26:56,028
I couldn't in good conscience
vote for a person...

1191
01:26:56,373 --> 01:26:58,333
...who doesn't believe in God.

1192
01:27:00,462 --> 01:27:01,782
Someone who...

1193
01:27:02,340 --> 01:27:05,300
...honestly thinks
the other 95%%% of us...

1194
01:27:05,637 --> 01:27:08,277
...suffer from some form
of mass delusion.

1195
01:27:11,812 --> 01:27:13,772
I told the truth up there.

1196
01:27:15,192 --> 01:27:18,512
Drumlin told you exactly
what you wanted to hear.

1197
01:27:53,791 --> 01:27:56,311
With full humility
and utmost gratitude...

1198
01:27:56,628 --> 01:27:58,668
...I accept this great honor...

1199
01:27:58,965 --> 01:28:02,885
...and I promise I will do my best
to represent my nation...

1200
01:28:03,263 --> 01:28:06,583
...my planet and my God
on this historic...

1201
01:28:06,893 --> 01:28:07,933
...journey.

1202
01:28:08,479 --> 01:28:10,719
I thank you
from the bottom of my heart.

1203
01:28:53,504 --> 01:28:56,344
There's a carnival atmosphere
at Cape Canaveral...

1204
01:28:56,633 --> 01:28:58,673
...as the International
Machine Consortium...

1205
01:28:58,970 --> 01:29:02,170
...hosts as much a media event
as a systems test.

1206
01:29:02,726 --> 01:29:06,326
David Drumlin is supervising
the on-site portion of the test.

1207
01:29:06,648 --> 01:29:08,448
We spoke with him earlier today.

1208
01:29:08,735 --> 01:29:10,415
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

1209
01:29:10,696 --> 01:29:13,496
...using the robot passenger...

1210
01:29:14,076 --> 01:29:16,356
... who we lovingly call Elmer.

1211
01:29:22,213 --> 01:29:24,573
The press wants to
ask you a few questions...

1212
01:29:24,883 --> 01:29:27,443
...as soon as they're done
with Dr. Drumlin.

1213
01:29:30,141 --> 01:29:31,901
When we release the pod...

1214
01:29:32,353 --> 01:29:34,713
...a substantial amount of energy
will be generated.

1215
01:29:35,566 --> 01:29:38,126
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

1216
01:29:38,445 --> 01:29:40,725
...using our robot passenger,
who we...

1217
01:29:41,074 --> 01:29:43,074
...lovingly call Elmer.

1218
01:29:43,744 --> 01:29:44,744
Thank you.

1219
01:29:44,996 --> 01:29:46,196
You're welcome.

1220
01:29:47,709 --> 01:29:49,869
They're ready for you
out at the site.

1221
01:29:50,630 --> 01:29:52,190
Yeah, just a minute.

1222
01:29:58,391 --> 01:30:00,591
-Congratulations.
-Glad you could come.

1223
01:30:01,980 --> 01:30:04,340
Didn't expect to see you here.

1224
01:30:05,193 --> 01:30:06,953
Well, I'm still...

1225
01:30:07,404 --> 01:30:09,924
...Crew Ops at the Control Center.

1226
01:30:10,701 --> 01:30:14,621
I suppose the fact that I discovered
the message means I have PR value.

1227
01:30:14,999 --> 01:30:16,359
Of course.

1228
01:30:18,128 --> 01:30:21,168
I know you must think
this is all very unfair.

1229
01:30:21,884 --> 01:30:23,804
And maybe that's an understatement.

1230
01:30:25,306 --> 01:30:27,546
What you don't know is, I agree.

1231
01:30:28,227 --> 01:30:31,347
I wish the world was a place
where fair was the bottom line...

1232
01:30:31,648 --> 01:30:34,848
...where the idealism you showed
at the hearing was rewarded...

1233
01:30:35,195 --> 01:30:37,235
...not taken advantage of.

1234
01:30:39,076 --> 01:30:41,796
Unfortunately,
we don't live in that world.

1235
01:30:44,250 --> 01:30:45,290
Funny...

1236
01:30:46,796 --> 01:30:49,796
...I always believed the world
is what we make of it.

1237
01:30:51,928 --> 01:30:52,728
Excuse me!

1238
01:30:56,685 --> 01:30:58,205
Good luck on the test.

1239
01:30:58,980 --> 01:31:00,100
Thank you.

1240
01:31:08,703 --> 01:31:09,703
Test director...

1241
01:31:09,955 --> 01:31:12,115
...everything looks good.
Ready to go.

1242
01:31:12,709 --> 01:31:15,629
I want things double
and triple-checked here.

1243
01:31:15,964 --> 01:31:19,044
We only get one shot at this.
Let's get it right.

1244
01:31:19,719 --> 01:31:22,599
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are ready for start-up.

1245
01:31:22,932 --> 01:31:26,132
All controllers, I need a go-no-go
for test initiation.

1246
01:31:26,521 --> 01:31:27,401
-Mechanical?
-Go.

1247
01:31:27,689 --> 01:31:28,609
Electrical?

1248
01:31:28,816 --> 01:31:29,816
Dynamics?

1249
01:31:30,068 --> 01:31:31,228
Communications?

1250
01:31:31,528 --> 01:31:32,608
Pod systems?

1251
01:31:32,822 --> 01:31:33,942
Safety?

1252
01:31:34,449 --> 01:31:37,169
Crew Ops, verify all pre-test
procedures are complete.

1253
01:31:37,579 --> 01:31:38,899
Yes, verified.
I'm go.

1254
01:31:39,164 --> 01:31:41,564
Pad Leader,
is everything okay with you?

1255
01:31:41,835 --> 01:31:44,315
Roger. The pad is a go.

1256
01:31:44,714 --> 01:31:47,314
Test initiation, on my mark.

1257
01:31:47,927 --> 01:31:49,127
5...

1258
01:31:49,555 --> 01:31:50,675
...4...

1259
01:31:51,099 --> 01:31:52,219
...3...

1260
01:31:52,559 --> 01:31:53,519
...2...

1261
01:31:54,103 --> 01:31:55,143
...1 .

1262
01:31:55,730 --> 01:31:56,810
Mark.

1263
01:31:57,358 --> 01:31:59,078
-Test start.
-Rings are unlocked.

1264
01:31:59,361 --> 01:32:00,881
Power levels show a good start.

1265
01:32:01,113 --> 01:32:02,873
We've begun the test of...

1266
01:32:03,116 --> 01:32:07,516
...earth's first system built by sharing
knowledge with a neighbor in space.

1267
01:32:07,873 --> 01:32:10,033
All power sources
on core induction bus.

1268
01:32:10,294 --> 01:32:11,974
IPV power transfer.

1269
01:32:12,255 --> 01:32:15,295
Ring motion detect.
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

1270
01:32:16,970 --> 01:32:19,930
-Gerry, how are we looking?
-Looks good. We're underway.

1271
01:32:20,225 --> 01:32:21,945
Looks like a normal start-up.

1272
01:32:22,228 --> 01:32:24,508
Roger, David.
It's looking good here.

1273
01:32:30,156 --> 01:32:33,396
We are moments away from
the initiation of the drop sequence.

1274
01:32:33,787 --> 01:32:35,427
All systems are go.

1275
01:32:38,502 --> 01:32:40,262
-Mechanical, you still happy?
-Roger.

1276
01:32:40,505 --> 01:32:41,785
It's very exciting...

1277
01:32:42,007 --> 01:32:43,567
...from up here.

1278
01:32:45,971 --> 01:32:47,651
We've got 4%.

1279
01:32:50,937 --> 01:32:53,537
Frequency 9.85.

1280
01:32:54,651 --> 01:32:56,571
Harmonics in the green.

1281
01:32:56,862 --> 01:32:59,062
G-level 1. 1.

1282
01:33:00,326 --> 01:33:03,566
-5%.
-Confirmed. We are at 5%.

1283
01:33:03,873 --> 01:33:05,433
David, how's it looking to you?

1284
01:33:05,792 --> 01:33:08,632
Okay. I'm going to take a look
and show you what we got.

1285
01:33:08,922 --> 01:33:10,682
Instrumentation looks good.

1286
01:33:10,925 --> 01:33:14,285
We have a good picture
from Dr. Drumlin's PRD.

1287
01:33:14,972 --> 01:33:17,292
Hope you guys are seeing
what I'm seeing.

1288
01:33:17,935 --> 01:33:19,695
All systems are go.

1289
01:33:21,315 --> 01:33:22,835
This is really something!

1290
01:33:23,067 --> 01:33:24,627
For purposes of this test...

1291
01:33:24,904 --> 01:33:29,024
...Dr. Drumlin will be on top of the
Gantry crane that's over the Machine.

1292
01:33:29,410 --> 01:33:31,370
We've got some video animation...

1293
01:33:31,705 --> 01:33:34,985
...to show just how this Machine...
it is thought... will work.

1294
01:33:35,336 --> 01:33:36,936
The passenger pod will release.

1295
01:33:37,213 --> 01:33:39,453
It will come down
through the center of the rings...

1296
01:33:39,759 --> 01:33:41,519
...and into the Machine's core.

1297
01:33:41,803 --> 01:33:44,003
The question everyone
here is asking is...

1298
01:33:44,349 --> 01:33:45,789
... what happens then?

1299
01:33:46,060 --> 01:33:47,620
Some believe the rings function...

1300
01:33:47,896 --> 01:33:50,736
...as some sort of an accelerator
or something...

1301
01:33:51,610 --> 01:33:53,690
...sending its energy
into the pod...

1302
01:33:53,946 --> 01:33:56,346
...making it rocket away
at near light speed.

1303
01:33:56,659 --> 01:34:00,979
Others believe it might open up
a doorway to some other dimension.

1304
01:34:01,457 --> 01:34:02,417
Who's right?

1305
01:34:02,751 --> 01:34:05,031
That's what
today's test is all about.

1306
01:34:05,588 --> 01:34:07,668
-35%%%.
-Subsystems ready?

1307
01:34:07,967 --> 01:34:09,807
40%%% normal acceleration.

1308
01:34:11,597 --> 01:34:14,437
Controllers stand by
to initiate drop sequence...

1309
01:34:14,810 --> 01:34:16,250
...on my mark.

1310
01:34:16,521 --> 01:34:18,601
All systems ready for drop sequence.

1311
01:34:18,983 --> 01:34:20,463
45%%%.

1312
01:34:24,533 --> 01:34:26,533
Verify closure.

1313
01:34:27,913 --> 01:34:29,153
46.

1314
01:34:29,624 --> 01:34:34,104
All controllers stand by to initiate
IPV drop sequence. On my mark.

1315
01:34:34,965 --> 01:34:36,285
48%%%.

1316
01:34:37,594 --> 01:34:39,674
I'm feeling
a very strange vibration.

1317
01:34:40,223 --> 01:34:43,143
-Are you feeling it down there?
-Gerry, can you confirm?

1318
01:34:43,853 --> 01:34:45,053
Everything looks good.

1319
01:34:45,856 --> 01:34:46,736
Crew Ops?

1320
01:34:47,024 --> 01:34:47,904
Nothing wrong.

1321
01:34:48,109 --> 01:34:49,669
We see nothing abnormal here.

1322
01:34:49,945 --> 01:34:52,665
No good. Hold sequence.
I'll take a direct reading.

1323
01:34:53,242 --> 01:34:54,602
What's he talking about?

1324
01:34:54,911 --> 01:34:56,471
Can anyone say grandstanding?

1325
01:34:56,872 --> 01:34:58,792
He sure knows he's on TV!

1326
01:34:59,084 --> 01:35:01,924
Back home that's what we call
an overcooked ham.

1327
01:35:02,422 --> 01:35:04,502
I'm reading 10 kilohertz!

1328
01:35:04,968 --> 01:35:07,648
What do you read on the first
and second order G-levels?

1329
01:35:07,972 --> 01:35:09,532
G-levels are right on!

1330
01:35:11,435 --> 01:35:14,235
We confirm Drumlin's readings.
All normal. We're go.

1331
01:35:15,608 --> 01:35:18,168
I think we're okay,
but we'll let him finish.

1332
01:35:19,614 --> 01:35:22,854
-Mechanical, you still okay?
-Roger. Right on the money.

1333
01:35:23,411 --> 01:35:24,571
Security problem!

1334
01:35:25,999 --> 01:35:27,559
Ellie, are you sure?

1335
01:35:28,294 --> 01:35:29,854
He shouldn't be there.
I know him.

1336
01:35:30,130 --> 01:35:32,810
Gerry, execute the
rapid shutdown sequence.

1337
01:35:33,176 --> 01:35:36,216
Security, move emergency
response team into position.

1338
01:35:36,598 --> 01:35:38,358
Get Drumlin on a secure loop.

1339
01:35:38,684 --> 01:35:40,004
You got him.

1340
01:35:40,311 --> 01:35:42,671
-Can you hear me?
-Yes, I hear.

1341
01:35:43,191 --> 01:35:45,231
We've got a security breach here.

1342
01:35:45,694 --> 01:35:46,654
Behind you.

1343
01:35:46,946 --> 01:35:47,786
The tall guy.

1344
01:35:48,240 --> 01:35:49,520
The technician.

1345
01:35:49,951 --> 01:35:50,991
See him?

1346
01:35:53,497 --> 01:35:54,697
He shouldn't be there.

1347
01:36:00,842 --> 01:36:02,242
Something's in his hand!

1348
01:36:03,429 --> 01:36:06,189
Him! Take him!
Security breach!

1349
01:36:06,600 --> 01:36:07,400
A bomb!

1350
01:36:07,727 --> 01:36:10,967
I want that emergency response team
up on the gantry. Now!

1351
01:36:11,441 --> 01:36:12,361
Stage One Alert!

1352
01:36:12,609 --> 01:36:15,249
Move all fire and rescue personnel
into position one.

1353
01:36:53,669 --> 01:36:55,709
All right, back to your stations.

1354
01:36:56,048 --> 01:36:59,008
I need you to be professional.
Settle down!

1355
01:36:59,303 --> 01:37:01,663
Pad Leader, do you copy?

1356
01:37:19,708 --> 01:37:22,188
The scene earlier today,
when David Drumlin...

1357
01:37:22,462 --> 01:37:24,302
...advisor to two Presidents...

1358
01:37:24,548 --> 01:37:28,268
...and winner of the National Academy
of Sciences lifetime award...

1359
01:37:28,721 --> 01:37:32,241
... was laid to rest
at Arlington National Cemetery.

1360
01:37:36,232 --> 01:37:37,912
In a related story...

1361
01:37:38,193 --> 01:37:39,433
Can I help you?

1362
01:37:41,490 --> 01:37:43,370
I've got some mail for you.

1363
01:37:43,827 --> 01:37:48,227
...the apparent suicide note of the
terrorist now believed responsible...

1364
01:37:48,584 --> 01:37:51,384
...for the explosion
in Florida this week.

1365
01:37:51,838 --> 01:37:53,398
What we do...

1366
01:37:53,758 --> 01:37:56,558
... we do for the goodness
of all mankind.

1367
01:37:57,472 --> 01:38:00,192
This won't be understood,
not now...

1368
01:38:00,685 --> 01:38:02,365
...but the Apocalypse to come...

1369
01:38:03,522 --> 01:38:05,602
... will vindicate our faith.

1370
01:38:30,061 --> 01:38:30,861
Welcome home.

1371
01:39:37,661 --> 01:39:39,141
Comrade Arroway...

1372
01:39:40,206 --> 01:39:43,446
... we have been expecting your call.
One moment, please.

1373
01:39:53,351 --> 01:39:54,511
Mr. Hadden?

1374
01:39:55,145 --> 01:39:56,465
Doctor!

1375
01:39:57,607 --> 01:39:59,367
How kind of you to call.

1376
01:40:00,069 --> 01:40:01,989
Mr. Hadden, where are you?

1377
01:40:04,283 --> 01:40:05,283
The Russian government...

1378
01:40:05,494 --> 01:40:08,734
... was kind enough
to give me accommodations on Mir.

1379
01:40:09,875 --> 01:40:11,635
You're living on a space station?

1380
01:40:13,088 --> 01:40:15,008
It's quite simple, really.

1381
01:40:16,552 --> 01:40:19,872
The low oxygen,
zero gravity environment...

1382
01:40:20,224 --> 01:40:24,704
...is the only thing keeping
the cancer from eating me alive.

1383
01:40:26,566 --> 01:40:29,086
Actually, I quite like it up here.

1384
01:40:29,738 --> 01:40:32,778
My little room
has one hell of a view.

1385
01:40:41,046 --> 01:40:42,806
I want to show you something.

1386
01:40:47,597 --> 01:40:49,517
Hokkaido Island.

1387
01:40:50,894 --> 01:40:53,014
The systems integration site.

1388
01:40:54,232 --> 01:40:55,712
Look closer.

1389
01:41:04,122 --> 01:41:06,842
First rule in government spending:

1390
01:41:07,961 --> 01:41:11,641
Why build one when you can have
two at twice the price?

1391
01:41:12,133 --> 01:41:15,013
Only, this one can be kept secret.

1392
01:41:15,806 --> 01:41:17,766
Controlled by Americans...

1393
01:41:18,267 --> 01:41:21,507
...built by Japanese
subcontractors...

1394
01:41:22,565 --> 01:41:25,085
... who also happen to be...

1395
01:41:26,154 --> 01:41:27,754
...recently acquired...

1396
01:41:28,366 --> 01:41:30,766
... wholly-owned subsidiaries...

1397
01:41:31,704 --> 01:41:33,624
...of Hadden Industries.

1398
01:41:37,337 --> 01:41:40,417
They still want
an American to go, Doctor.

1399
01:41:44,306 --> 01:41:45,786
Want to take a ride?

1400
01:42:28,579 --> 01:42:30,499
Augmenting our restraint and...

1401
01:42:30,791 --> 01:42:32,831
...communications console
subsystem...

1402
01:42:33,086 --> 01:42:35,006
...is your personal recording unit.

1403
01:42:35,381 --> 01:42:38,781
Normal,
infrared and ultraviolet lenses.

1404
01:42:39,596 --> 01:42:43,316
Digital microchip good for
thousands of hours of recording.

1405
01:42:44,812 --> 01:42:46,892
Okay, look, I understand...

1406
01:42:47,232 --> 01:42:50,472
...the reason for recording
and documenting the mission.

1407
01:42:50,820 --> 01:42:53,220
But I just want to go on record
one more time.

1408
01:42:53,616 --> 01:42:56,936
The transmitted specs never said
anything about any chair...

1409
01:42:57,288 --> 01:42:59,128
...or a restraining harness...

1410
01:42:59,416 --> 01:43:01,336
...or survival gear.

1411
01:43:02,129 --> 01:43:03,889
Why can't we just trust
the original...

1412
01:43:04,132 --> 01:43:07,972
Doctor, both the IMC Board and
the SI team reviewed the matter...

1413
01:43:08,305 --> 01:43:11,745
...and concluded that the design
impact is negligible.

1414
01:43:12,269 --> 01:43:13,749
Bottom line is...

1415
01:43:14,313 --> 01:43:16,393
...we're not putting anyone
aboard this Machine...

1416
01:43:16,692 --> 01:43:19,572
...unless there is
some sort of minimal protection.

1417
01:43:19,988 --> 01:43:21,268
End of story.

1418
01:43:28,334 --> 01:43:32,174
We've given these to the astronauts
since the start of the space program.

1419
01:43:33,717 --> 01:43:35,917
It's never been made public,
of course.

1420
01:43:36,179 --> 01:43:38,219
It's fast and it's painless.

1421
01:43:41,019 --> 01:43:43,899
I'm going to travel 26 light years
to commit suicide?

1422
01:43:44,316 --> 01:43:45,956
Something may go wrong.

1423
01:43:46,528 --> 01:43:49,088
There may be
an unforeseen mechanical failure.

1424
01:43:50,033 --> 01:43:52,913
You could be marooned,
unable to return.

1425
01:43:54,206 --> 01:43:57,246
There are 1,000 reasons
we can think of to have this...

1426
01:43:57,544 --> 01:44:00,384
...but mostly it's for the reasons
we can't think of.

1427
01:44:27,087 --> 01:44:28,167
Come in.

1428
01:44:29,758 --> 01:44:31,998
Dr. Arroway, time to get ready.

1429
01:44:32,262 --> 01:44:33,222
Thank you.

1430
01:44:44,404 --> 01:44:46,044
I know there's not much time.

1431
01:44:46,282 --> 01:44:49,242
As soon as I found out about it,
I called the President.

1432
01:44:49,579 --> 01:44:51,179
I came with Kitz.

1433
01:44:51,832 --> 01:44:54,032
I had to see you one more time.

1434
01:44:54,294 --> 01:44:55,934
Oh, God, I'm sorry.

1435
01:44:56,422 --> 01:44:58,062
No, I'm glad you came.

1436
01:44:58,425 --> 01:45:00,545
There's something
I got to say to you.

1437
01:45:02,014 --> 01:45:06,094
The reason I didn't vote for you was
a good one, but not the real one.

1438
01:45:07,313 --> 01:45:09,233
I didn't vote for you to go...

1439
01:45:11,194 --> 01:45:12,994
...because I don't want to lose you.

1440
01:45:14,157 --> 01:45:16,237
Now you find your way home,
all right?

1441
01:45:33,352 --> 01:45:34,752
23 hours ago, the world...

1442
01:45:35,021 --> 01:45:38,981
... was stunned by the announcement
of the existence of another Machine...

1443
01:45:39,319 --> 01:45:42,159
...and its passenger,
Eleanor Ann Arroway.

1444
01:45:42,490 --> 01:45:43,050
Now...

1445
01:45:43,700 --> 01:45:46,060
...the question
that's on everyone's mind:

1446
01:45:46,329 --> 01:45:48,009
Will history repeat itself?

1447
01:45:48,499 --> 01:45:50,739
With a piece of engineering
this complex...

1448
01:45:51,044 --> 01:45:54,884
... with so many unknowns,
could the unthinkable occur?

1449
01:45:55,217 --> 01:45:58,417
The security in Hokkaido
has been incredibly tight.

1450
01:45:58,722 --> 01:46:02,002
No reporters whatsoever
have been allowed near the site.

1451
01:48:42,714 --> 01:48:45,594
Restraint secure.
Life support functions normal.

1452
01:48:45,927 --> 01:48:46,767
Roger.

1453
01:48:46,970 --> 01:48:48,930
This is Control.
Do you copy?

1454
01:48:49,307 --> 01:48:50,627
Reading you five-by-five.

1455
01:48:51,769 --> 01:48:53,209
Give me Ellie's PRD.

1456
01:48:53,480 --> 01:48:55,400
Video unit recording
and transmitting.

1457
01:48:56,818 --> 01:48:59,338
-Are you reading me?
-That's affirmative.

1458
01:48:59,614 --> 01:49:01,254
Video looks good.

1459
01:49:02,159 --> 01:49:03,239
Copy, Control.

1460
01:49:04,663 --> 01:49:07,383
Ellie, we're going to proceed
to button you up.

1461
01:49:09,378 --> 01:49:10,458
I'm ready.

1462
01:49:14,385 --> 01:49:16,145
Confirming walkway retraction.

1463
01:49:16,931 --> 01:49:18,291
-Communications?
-Go.

1464
01:49:18,517 --> 01:49:20,437
-Life support?
-Go.

1465
01:49:20,853 --> 01:49:22,213
We are go for closure.

1466
01:49:24,692 --> 01:49:26,332
I'm go here.

1467
01:49:27,446 --> 01:49:30,766
Mechanical, initiate
IPV closure sequence.

1468
01:49:32,537 --> 01:49:34,217
Let me get you a chair.

1469
01:49:36,710 --> 01:49:39,910
-lt's nice to smell you again, Mr. Kitz.
-You too.

1470
01:49:40,758 --> 01:49:42,518
Wouldn't peg him as a Polo man.

1471
01:49:51,983 --> 01:49:53,423
I got a visual on the door.

1472
01:49:55,905 --> 01:49:57,665
The door is looking good.

1473
01:50:02,999 --> 01:50:04,599
Door alignment looks good.

1474
01:50:33,919 --> 01:50:35,359
We're green across the board.

1475
01:50:35,630 --> 01:50:38,030
Copy that, Control.
IPV is secure.

1476
01:50:48,149 --> 01:50:49,469
Copy that, 30%.

1477
01:50:54,366 --> 01:50:55,766
How you doing in there?

1478
01:50:56,369 --> 01:50:56,969
Kent?

1479
01:50:57,913 --> 01:50:58,633
Is that you?

1480
01:50:59,081 --> 01:51:00,601
That's a big affirmative.

1481
01:51:01,543 --> 01:51:02,983
Who let you in there?

1482
01:51:03,379 --> 01:51:05,299
A higher power intervened.

1483
01:51:07,427 --> 01:51:08,787
I'm glad you came.

1484
01:51:13,519 --> 01:51:14,639
35%.

1485
01:51:15,481 --> 01:51:16,761
Copy that, 35%.

1486
01:51:17,066 --> 01:51:18,466
-Mechanical?
-We're good.

1487
01:51:18,694 --> 01:51:20,014
40%.

1488
01:51:23,576 --> 01:51:25,496
I'm picking up a moderate vibration.

1489
01:51:26,747 --> 01:51:28,707
Dynamics, can you confirm vibration?

1490
01:51:29,000 --> 01:51:30,160
It looks good here.

1491
01:51:30,461 --> 01:51:33,541
She's feeling the same thing
they felt at the Cape.

1492
01:51:33,841 --> 01:51:34,881
Vibration's normal.

1493
01:51:38,348 --> 01:51:40,068
Copy that, 50%.

1494
01:51:45,608 --> 01:51:47,448
Vibration's a little stronger now.

1495
01:51:47,820 --> 01:51:50,020
We're picking up
some low frequency noise.

1496
01:51:50,949 --> 01:51:52,429
Mechanical, confirm?

1497
01:51:52,702 --> 01:51:54,022
It looks fine to me.

1498
01:51:54,288 --> 01:51:56,368
Roger.
Jerry, what do you think?

1499
01:51:56,666 --> 01:51:57,506
I'm still go.

1500
01:51:57,751 --> 01:51:59,231
People, we are still go.

1501
01:52:02,091 --> 01:52:03,571
Something's happening.

1502
01:52:07,724 --> 01:52:09,084
You see that light?

1503
01:52:09,393 --> 01:52:10,473
I'm seeing...

1504
01:52:13,775 --> 01:52:15,655
I can't tell if it's daylight.

1505
01:52:16,529 --> 01:52:18,929
There it is again.
It's coming from the bottom.

1506
01:52:20,493 --> 01:52:22,013
Let me show you.
See that?

1507
01:52:22,287 --> 01:52:24,407
Negative.
You're breaking up.

1508
01:52:24,833 --> 01:52:26,913
-Can we boost signal?
-lt's at maximum.

1509
01:52:27,503 --> 01:52:28,743
65%%%.

1510
01:52:28,964 --> 01:52:30,604
The material is changing.

1511
01:52:30,842 --> 01:52:34,202
It's bordering on translucence.
The system's intact.

1512
01:52:37,685 --> 01:52:39,165
It has to be...

1513
01:52:39,479 --> 01:52:41,839
...some kind of
electromagnetic field.

1514
01:52:42,192 --> 01:52:43,232
Do you read this?

1515
01:52:43,527 --> 01:52:45,047
We see only interference.

1516
01:52:45,279 --> 01:52:46,999
It's becoming translucent.

1517
01:52:47,950 --> 01:52:50,390
I can't describe it.
I can't even explain it!

1518
01:52:53,208 --> 01:52:54,128
70%%%.

1519
01:52:54,376 --> 01:52:56,656
We have intermittent comm,
but we are go!

1520
01:52:57,089 --> 01:52:59,009
Initiate secondary drive systems.

1521
01:52:59,300 --> 01:53:01,260
Initiating
auxiliary booster sequence.

