1606
02:00:11,437 --> 02:00:12,517
...a poet.

1607
02:00:13,106 --> 02:00:14,506
It's so beautiful!

1608
02:00:15,818 --> 02:00:17,058
Beautiful!

1609
02:00:18,906 --> 02:00:20,666
So beautiful.

1610
02:00:25,290 --> 02:00:27,650
I had no idea.

1611
02:03:07,362 --> 02:03:08,602
Hi, Sparks.

1612
02:03:10,534 --> 02:03:11,494
Dad?

1613
02:03:19,547 --> 02:03:21,027
I missed you.

1614
02:03:27,100 --> 02:03:28,060
Aren't you...?

1615
02:03:28,310 --> 02:03:31,070
I'm sorry I couldn't
be there for you, sweetheart.

1616
02:03:41,413 --> 02:03:42,693
You're not real.

1617
02:03:44,751 --> 02:03:46,111
None of this is real!

1618
02:03:46,420 --> 02:03:48,060
That's my scientist.

1619
02:03:49,508 --> 02:03:53,628
When I was unconscious, you
downloaded my thoughts, my memories.

1620
02:03:54,807 --> 02:03:56,087
Pensacola!

1621
02:03:59,439 --> 02:04:01,799
We thought it might
make things easier for you.

1622
02:04:15,713 --> 02:04:17,113
Why did you contact us?

1623
02:04:17,341 --> 02:04:18,941
You contacted us.

1624
02:04:19,552 --> 02:04:21,112
We were just listening.

1625
02:04:22,014 --> 02:04:23,294
There are others?

1626
02:04:23,683 --> 02:04:24,803
Many others.

1627
02:04:29,984 --> 02:04:31,144
They all...

1628
02:04:31,695 --> 02:04:34,735
...travel here through
that transit system you built?

1629
02:04:35,325 --> 02:04:36,805
We didn't build it.

1630
02:04:37,996 --> 02:04:39,476
We don't know who did.

1631
02:04:41,585 --> 02:04:44,105
They were gone
long before we ever got here.

1632
02:04:45,173 --> 02:04:46,933
Maybe someday they'll come back.

1633
02:04:48,011 --> 02:04:50,491
All the civilizations
you find come here?

1634
02:04:50,765 --> 02:04:51,965
Not all.

1635
02:04:53,769 --> 02:04:56,769
-ls this some test?
-No, no test.

1636
02:04:59,903 --> 02:05:01,343
You have your mother's hands.

1637
02:05:11,629 --> 02:05:13,709
You're an interesting species...

1638
02:05:14,425 --> 02:05:16,025
...an interesting mix.

1639
02:05:17,387 --> 02:05:19,987
You're capable
of such beautiful dreams...

1640
02:05:21,143 --> 02:05:23,183
...and such horrible nightmares.

1641
02:05:24,815 --> 02:05:26,575
You feel so lost...

1642
02:05:27,402 --> 02:05:29,842
...so cut off, so alone.

1643
02:05:31,658 --> 02:05:32,898
Only you're not.

1644
02:05:37,459 --> 02:05:39,059
In all our searching...

1645
02:05:39,295 --> 02:05:42,135
...all we've found
that makes the emptiness bearable...

1646
02:05:42,967 --> 02:05:44,367
...is each other.

1647
02:05:48,350 --> 02:05:49,910
What happens now?

1648
02:05:51,312 --> 02:05:52,392
Now?

1649
02:05:53,816 --> 02:05:55,216
You go home.

1650
02:05:55,819 --> 02:05:56,819
Home?

1651
02:05:57,321 --> 02:05:58,401
But...

1652
02:05:58,990 --> 02:06:00,350
...I have so many questions.

1653
02:06:00,826 --> 02:06:02,386
Do we get to come back?

1654
02:06:03,539 --> 02:06:05,299
This was just a first step.

1655
02:06:06,001 --> 02:06:07,721
In time, you'll take another.

1656
02:06:09,339 --> 02:06:11,779
But other people need to see
what I've seen...

1657
02:06:12,051 --> 02:06:14,971
This is the way it's been done
for billions of years.

1658
02:06:17,476 --> 02:06:19,076
Small moves, Ellie.

1659
02:06:21,023 --> 02:06:22,623
Small moves.

1660
02:07:06,214 --> 02:07:07,814
We've got video on Ellie!

1661
02:07:08,092 --> 02:07:09,972
She's through!
She is in the net.

1662
02:07:10,220 --> 02:07:12,500
She's alive.
Get the President on the phone!

1663
02:07:13,433 --> 02:07:14,913
What's going on?
How is she?

1664
02:07:15,812 --> 02:07:17,452
Ellie, this is Control.
You copy?

1665
02:07:17,773 --> 02:07:19,133
-What's going on?
-I don't know.

1666
02:07:19,943 --> 02:07:21,463
-She's alive.
-Put her on P.A.

1667
02:07:21,779 --> 02:07:23,219
Ellie, hold on tight.

1668
02:07:23,949 --> 02:07:27,109
We're still trying to determine
the nature of the malfunction...

1669
02:07:27,454 --> 02:07:29,894
...but the important thing
is you're okay.

1670
02:07:30,250 --> 02:07:31,210
What?

1671
02:07:31,585 --> 02:07:32,985
It's all right.

1672
02:07:33,254 --> 02:07:35,054
The important thing is you're safe.

1673
02:07:36,133 --> 02:07:37,893
What malfunction?

1674
02:07:42,351 --> 02:07:43,631
What happened?

1675
02:07:45,314 --> 02:07:46,794
What day is this?

1676
02:07:47,650 --> 02:07:48,610
I'm sorry.

1677
02:07:48,860 --> 02:07:50,260
Did you say what day?

1678
02:07:51,990 --> 02:07:53,430
How long was I gone?

1679
02:07:55,829 --> 02:07:59,829
The IPV dropped
straight through the Machine.

1680
02:08:00,878 --> 02:08:02,558
You didn't go anywhere.

1681
02:08:03,340 --> 02:08:04,620
But I did.

1682
02:08:05,009 --> 02:08:06,249
I did go.

1683
02:08:06,845 --> 02:08:08,925
That's what I've tried
to tell everyone.

1684
02:08:13,647 --> 02:08:16,087
But the headset
didn't record a single image?

1685
02:08:16,902 --> 02:08:18,142
Just this.

1686
02:08:18,487 --> 02:08:19,487
Static.

1687
02:08:19,698 --> 02:08:20,658
Thank you.

1688
02:08:22,201 --> 02:08:23,841
Let me show you what we saw.

1689
02:08:33,927 --> 02:08:37,407
43 separate remote cameras
show exactly the same event.

1690
02:08:37,891 --> 02:08:41,211
The IPV dropped straight through.
Everyone saw exactly...

1691
02:08:41,688 --> 02:08:43,008
...the same thing.

1692
02:08:43,399 --> 02:08:44,839
Nothing happened.

1693
02:08:46,529 --> 02:08:48,449
How do you explain this, Doctor?

1694
02:08:50,743 --> 02:08:51,903
I can't.

1695
02:08:52,120 --> 02:08:53,520
I'd encourage you...

1696
02:08:55,375 --> 02:08:57,495
...not to inflame this situation...

1697
02:08:57,754 --> 02:08:59,514
...beyond the facts.

1698
02:08:59,757 --> 02:09:02,837
Let us deal with this on the facts.

1699
02:09:03,262 --> 02:09:06,142
We are monitoring
what has actually happened.

1700
02:09:06,433 --> 02:09:09,393
We are taking
what we believe are factually...

1701
02:09:09,730 --> 02:09:11,650
...appropriate steps.

1702
02:09:12,025 --> 02:09:14,985
Amid a flurry of accusations
and counter-accusations...

1703
02:09:15,279 --> 02:09:17,839
...by the nations representing
the Machine Consortium...

1704
02:09:18,159 --> 02:09:20,879
...the President has ordered
a special inquiry.

1705
02:09:21,163 --> 02:09:23,883
But the appointment
to the committee of Michael Kitz...

1706
02:09:24,168 --> 02:09:26,888
... who has resigned
as National Security Advisor...

1707
02:09:27,214 --> 02:09:29,534
...has raised eyebrows
on Capitol Hill.

1708
02:09:29,843 --> 02:09:33,363
I have made no decision to run for
Congress, announced no candidacy.

1709
02:09:33,765 --> 02:09:36,965
I resigned as
National Security Advisor...

1710
02:09:37,312 --> 02:09:41,272
...in order to devote
all of my energy to this inquiry.

1711
02:09:42,194 --> 02:09:46,634
The people of the world have a right
to know what really happened.

1712
02:09:47,660 --> 02:09:50,220
Yet every scientific
instrument confirms...

1713
02:09:50,498 --> 02:09:54,338
...the IPV was out of contact
for only a fraction of a second.

1714
02:09:54,671 --> 02:09:56,431
Isn't that correct, Doctor?

1715
02:09:58,468 --> 02:10:00,708
A fraction of a second Earth time,
yes.

1716
02:10:01,639 --> 02:10:02,959
Earth time?

1717
02:10:03,225 --> 02:10:06,545
Senator, I believe that the Machine
opened up a wormhole...

1718
02:10:07,064 --> 02:10:11,504
...a tunnel through space-time, also
known as an Einstein-Rossen Bridge.

1719
02:10:12,030 --> 02:10:16,030
Due to the effect of general relativity,
what I experienced as 18 hours...

1720
02:10:16,369 --> 02:10:18,569
...passed instantaneously on Earth.

1721
02:10:18,873 --> 02:10:22,833
Isn't it true these wormholes
are merely theoretical predictions?

1722
02:10:23,380 --> 02:10:25,900
There is no evidence
they actually exist?

1723
02:10:26,217 --> 02:10:27,817
There is no direct evidence, no.

1724
02:10:28,220 --> 02:10:29,340
Tell me...

1725
02:10:29,848 --> 02:10:32,688
...why would these aliens
go to all this trouble?

1726
02:10:33,394 --> 02:10:37,274
Bring you thousands of light years,
then send you home without proof?

1727
02:10:38,110 --> 02:10:40,750
They said it's how it's been done
for billions of years.

1728
02:10:41,406 --> 02:10:44,566
You have no proof because
they didn't want you to have any.

1729
02:10:45,078 --> 02:10:46,958
A phenomenon known
in psychiatric circles...

1730
02:10:47,207 --> 02:10:49,487
...as a self-reinforcing delusion.

1731
02:10:50,420 --> 02:10:51,820
You think I was delusional?

1732
02:10:52,130 --> 02:10:56,090
I do think you may have suffered
some kind of an episode. Yes, I do.

1733
02:10:56,428 --> 02:10:59,148
I'd like to propose
an alternate hypothesis...

1734
02:10:59,433 --> 02:11:02,993
...and I'd like you to bring your
scientific expertise to bear on it.

1735
02:11:03,439 --> 02:11:06,319
To fake a signal from Vega...

1736
02:11:07,236 --> 02:11:08,476
...what would you need?

1737
02:11:10,449 --> 02:11:14,089
You'd need a satellite to transmit
it, but it would be impossible to...

1738
02:11:14,455 --> 02:11:18,255
You'd need a satellite
and launch capabilities to orbit it.

1739
02:11:18,586 --> 02:11:21,706
And the message itself. To put
something like this together...

1740
02:11:22,091 --> 02:11:24,291
...so complex,
drawing on many disciplines...

1741
02:11:24,553 --> 02:11:25,833
Would be impossible.

1742
02:11:27,725 --> 02:11:29,205
Impossible?

1743
02:11:29,727 --> 02:11:32,527
Is there anyone who might
have been up to the challenge?

1744
02:11:33,566 --> 02:11:36,006
Someone with extraordinary
technical expertise...

1745
02:11:36,362 --> 02:11:38,282
...enormous financial resources...

1746
02:11:38,824 --> 02:11:42,744
...someone perverse enough, eccentric
enough to come up with the idea?

1747
02:11:44,624 --> 02:11:45,344
Hadden?

1748
02:11:46,502 --> 02:11:48,422
S. R. Hadden.

1749
02:11:53,012 --> 02:11:54,612
You're implying that this was...

1750
02:11:54,890 --> 02:11:57,370
...some kind of a hoax?
That he engineered this?

1751
02:11:57,644 --> 02:11:58,924
S. R. Hadden...

1752
02:11:59,354 --> 02:12:03,674
...a legendary power broker in
perhaps his final bid for immortality.

1753
02:12:04,195 --> 02:12:06,755
Maybe he wanted to
exploit new technologies...

1754
02:12:07,032 --> 02:12:09,152
...having world governments
pick up the tab.

1755
02:12:09,411 --> 02:12:12,091
Perhaps this was his
final altruistic gesture...

1756
02:12:12,415 --> 02:12:15,895
...to unite the world in some
common goal. Maybe all of the above.

1757
02:12:16,421 --> 02:12:18,461
S. R. Hadden, a brilliant...

1758
02:12:19,217 --> 02:12:20,817
...and complicated man.

1759
02:12:23,724 --> 02:12:27,404
Doctor, are you familiar
with the scientific precept...

1760
02:12:28,230 --> 02:12:30,230
...known as Occam's Razor?

1761
02:12:36,576 --> 02:12:37,656
Yes.

1762
02:12:39,706 --> 02:12:44,226
It means the simplest explanation
generally tends to be the right one.

1763
02:12:44,588 --> 02:12:45,548
Exactly.

1764
02:12:46,340 --> 02:12:48,740
You tell me.
What is more likely here?

1765
02:12:49,053 --> 02:12:52,293
A message from aliens
results in a magical machine...

1766
02:12:52,600 --> 02:12:55,200
...that whisks you
to the center of the galaxy...

1767
02:12:55,521 --> 02:12:58,241
...to windsurf with Dad
and a split second later...

1768
02:12:58,567 --> 02:13:01,927
...returns you home
without a single shred of proof?

1769
02:13:02,489 --> 02:13:05,809
Or that your experience
is the result of being...

1770
02:13:06,119 --> 02:13:09,439
...the unwitting star in the
farewell performance of one...

1771
02:13:09,750 --> 02:13:10,670
...S.R. Hadden?

1772
02:13:10,918 --> 02:13:14,478
A man with the means and motive
to play you and all of us...

1773
02:13:14,799 --> 02:13:18,959
...as pawns in the most elaborate,
most expensive hoax of all time?

1774
02:13:24,146 --> 02:13:27,666
You come to us with no evidence,
no records...

1775
02:13:28,569 --> 02:13:30,249
...no artifacts...

1776
02:13:30,656 --> 02:13:34,656
...only a story that, to put it
mildly, strains credibility.

1777
02:13:36,122 --> 02:13:39,002
Over half a trillion dollars
were spent.

1778
02:13:39,460 --> 02:13:41,820
Dozens of lives were lost.

1779
02:13:43,007 --> 02:13:47,207
Are you going to sit there and tell
us we should just take this all...

1780
02:13:48,474 --> 02:13:49,834
...on faith?

1781
02:13:53,940 --> 02:13:55,860
Please answer the question, Doctor.

1782
02:13:59,824 --> 02:14:01,904
Is it possible
that it didn't happen?

1783
02:14:02,244 --> 02:14:03,324
Yes.

1784
02:14:06,208 --> 02:14:09,248
As a scientist I must concede that.
I must volunteer that.

1785
02:14:13,844 --> 02:14:15,164
Let me get this straight.

1786
02:14:15,555 --> 02:14:19,395
You admit you have no physical
evidence to back up your story?

1787
02:14:20,145 --> 02:14:20,945
Yes.

1788
02:14:21,230 --> 02:14:24,150
You admit you may have
hallucinated this whole thing?

1789
02:14:25,194 --> 02:14:27,434
You admit if you were
in our position...

1790
02:14:27,698 --> 02:14:31,098
...you would be as incredulous
and skeptical as we?

1791
02:14:32,747 --> 02:14:36,587
Then why don't you simply withdraw
your testimony and concede...

1792
02:14:37,045 --> 02:14:40,965
...that this journey to the center
of the galaxy never took place?

1793
02:14:44,097 --> 02:14:45,857
Because I can't.

1794
02:14:52,902 --> 02:14:55,502
I had an experience.

1795
02:14:57,951 --> 02:15:00,511
I can't prove it.
I can't even explain it.

1796
02:15:00,788 --> 02:15:03,668
But everything I know as
a human being, everything I am...

1797
02:15:03,960 --> 02:15:06,040
...tells me it was real.

1798
02:15:08,592 --> 02:15:11,912
I was given something wonderful,
something that changed me forever.

1799
02:15:12,389 --> 02:15:13,429
A vision...

1800
02:15:14,016 --> 02:15:15,576
...of the universe...

1801
02:15:16,395 --> 02:15:18,475
...that tells us undeniably...

1802
02:15:19,024 --> 02:15:21,304
...how tiny and insignificant...

1803
02:15:21,569 --> 02:15:24,969
...and how rare and precious
we all are.

1804
02:15:26,284 --> 02:15:29,284
A vision that tells us
that we belong to something...

1805
02:15:29,664 --> 02:15:34,104
...that is greater than ourselves,
that none of us are alone.

1806
02:15:39,220 --> 02:15:42,100
I wish I could share that.

1807
02:15:45,771 --> 02:15:46,851
I wish...

1808
02:15:48,525 --> 02:15:50,885
...that everyone, if even for one...

1809
02:15:51,321 --> 02:15:52,481
...moment...

1810
02:15:52,782 --> 02:15:54,022
...could feel...

1811
02:15:54,534 --> 02:15:57,414
...that awe and humility and hope.

1812
02:16:06,927 --> 02:16:09,087
That continues to be my wish.

1813
02:16:50,408 --> 02:16:52,928
Dr. Arroway,
can I get a picture, please.

1814
02:17:35,099 --> 02:17:36,179
Reverend Joss!

1815
02:17:36,434 --> 02:17:37,994
What do you believe?!

1816
02:17:43,945 --> 02:17:47,785
As a person of faith, I'm bound by a
different covenant than Dr. Arroway.

1817
02:17:49,787 --> 02:17:51,867
But our goal is one and the same.

1818
02:17:52,458 --> 02:17:54,058
The pursuit of truth.

1819
02:17:57,674 --> 02:17:58,914
l, for one, believe her.

1820
02:18:22,502 --> 02:18:25,342
So what happens now?
We give her a medal?

1821
02:18:25,882 --> 02:18:28,202
I'd say at least a healthy grant.

1822
02:18:28,678 --> 02:18:31,958
You read the confidential report
from the investigating committee?

1823
02:18:32,308 --> 02:18:33,668
I flipped through it.

1824
02:18:34,186 --> 02:18:38,306
I was very interested in the section
on Arroway's video unit.

1825
02:18:39,193 --> 02:18:41,433
The one that recorded the static.

1826
02:18:42,866 --> 02:18:44,106
Continue.

1827
02:18:45,161 --> 02:18:48,401
The fact that it recorded static
isn't what interests me.

1828
02:18:53,882 --> 02:18:55,122
Continue.

1829
02:18:56,052 --> 02:18:57,852
What interests me...

1830
02:18:58,221 --> 02:19:01,781
...is that it recorded
approximately 18 hours of it.

1831
02:19:07,193 --> 02:19:08,993
That is interesting, isn't it?

1832
02:19:15,789 --> 02:19:19,589
And you can see over there,
we're building 45 brand new dishes.

1833
02:19:20,004 --> 02:19:23,684
That means when you put them together
with all the radio telescopes...

1834
02:19:24,051 --> 02:19:25,371
...all over the world...

1835
02:19:25,637 --> 02:19:29,837
...we'll hear farther into space
than anyone has ever heard before.

1836
02:19:31,562 --> 02:19:34,362
Are there other people
out there in the universe?

1837
02:19:35,443 --> 02:19:36,803
That's a good question.

1838
02:19:37,112 --> 02:19:38,192
What do you think?

1839
02:19:38,865 --> 02:19:39,825
I don't know.

1840
02:19:40,325 --> 02:19:41,805
That's a good answer.

1841
02:19:43,121 --> 02:19:44,081
Skeptic, huh?

1842
02:19:45,416 --> 02:19:49,776
The important thing is that you all
keep searching for your own answers.

1843
02:19:50,465 --> 02:19:52,425
One thing about the universe,
though.

1844
02:19:53,470 --> 02:19:54,590
The universe...

1845
02:19:55,139 --> 02:19:57,219
...is a pretty big place.

1846
02:19:58,310 --> 02:20:00,550
It's bigger than anything...

1847
02:20:01,022 --> 02:20:03,742
...anyone has ever
dreamed of before.

1848
02:20:05,445 --> 02:20:07,085
So if it's just us...

1849
02:20:08,992 --> 02:20:11,072
...it seems like
an awful waste of space.

1850
02:20:13,040 --> 02:20:14,000
Right?

